news.title: Surat civic body removes 71 illegal structures in two years
news.para: These figures came up as part of a reply to Congress MLA from Vansda, Anant Patel, in the assembly. Patel asked for these details after he came to know about rampant illegal constructions in the city.

news.title: Indore leads the race with 478.3 million sq ft in green building footprints and urban infrastructure in MP
news.para: Sustainable projects have encompassed approximately 500.4 million sq ft of eco-friendly footprints in Madhya Pradesh, with 478.3 million sq ft exclusively in Indore.

news.title: Realtor and 10 others booked for Rs 7 crore property fraud in Ludhiana
news.para: Between April and September 2022, the company transferred Rs 7.61 crore to Mann's account, expecting the funds to be used for purchasing land from several individuals.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government approves revised mobility plans in Vijayawada and Visakhapatnam
news.para: GO 215 authorises the consultant agency to prepare the revised CMP for Vijayawada Metro at a cost of 81.67 lakh, inclusive of 18% GST. Similarly, GO 216 grants permission to prepare the revised CMP for Visakhapatnam Metro at a cost of 84.47 lakh, inclusive of 18% GST.

news.title: Madras HC dismisses plea against Tidel park in Madurai
news.para: The court was hearing the petition filed by R Mayilsamy, Secretary of Neer Nilaigal Matrum Sutruchoozhal Paathukappu Nala Sangam-Madurai North.

news.title: About 25 illegal buildings on land notified for Noida airport razed in Jewar tehsil
news.para: Officials carried out a four-hour drive, targeting illegal houses and permanent structures on land notified for acquisition for the airport's third and fourth phases.

news.title: New master plans for Hyderabad development: Telangana minister
news.para: Sridhar Babu said there were five master plans for the Hyderabad metropolitan region earlier, and they are reaching their exhaustion date soon.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Price of riverfront plot up by over Rs 8,000 per sq meters in three months
news.para: The Sabarmati Riverfront Development Corporation Ltd (SRFDCL) successfully sold development rights at Rs 26,000 per sq m in Nov 2024.

news.title: Prayagraj development body likely to offer housing schemes in beautified areas
news.para: Under the leadership of PDA vice chairman Amit Pal Sharma, the authority has set up a special team to identify land beside or in the vicinity of the roads that were beautified for the Maha Kumbh.

news.title: Bengaluru: Mahadevapura leads Rs 390-crore property tax shortfall
news.para: Among BBMP zones, East follows Mahadevapura with Rs 25.81 crore spending, or 3.98% of the Rs 675.21 crore demanded, with Rs 649.40 crore collected and 46,153 properties overdue.

news.title: Bihar: 75,000 PMAY-Gramin beneficiaries get first instalment
news.para: The minister transferred the amount into the bank accounts of the beneficiaries digitally at a function in Patna. The landless beneficiaries got Rs1.20 lakh each while those having own land were paid Rs 40,000 each as the first instalment.

news.title: Brigade Group acquires 4.4 acres land in Whitefield, Bengaluru
news.para: Brigade Group will develop a residential project with a total development potential of 0.6 million sq ft and a gross development value of approximately Rs 950 crore.

news.title: Sunac China working on second restructuring of offshore debt
news.para: The company said in a filing on Monday it would seek a more comprehensive debt solution "to address its current offshore debt risks", citing the impact of a liquidation petition against the company, and weak market conditions.

news.title: Over Rs 800 crore spent on Jammu smart city project in six Years
news.para: The chief minister said though no major complaints were received with regard to the completed work under the mission, minor complaints raised by people were promptly addressed.

news.title: Ulhasnagar civic body orders inquiry into alleged property tax corruption
news.para: Vadhrya alleged that officials granted a 100% penalty waiver on property tax instead of the 50% limit set by the scheme, benefitting a businessman. He further claimed that tax department staff tampered with the property tax software to facilitate this.

news.title: Development works and PMAY-G housing surveys underway in Nowshera, Jammu and Kashmir
news.para: The Line-of-Control in Nowshera previously faced frequent shelling, which made development work extremely challenging in this region.

news.title: Ranchi civic body intensifies its holding tax collection drive for FY 2024-25
news.para: Assistant municipal commissioner Chandradeep Kumar said "Over Rs 2 lakh were collected, two unlicensed businesses sealed, and notices issued to defaulters during a week-long campaign earlier this year."

news.title: Mt. K Kapital to launch Rs 2,500 crore fund for housing projects across major cities
news.para: These five projects, with a total developable area of 7 lakh square feet, are located in Mumbai Metropolitan Region (MMR) and are being developed by Keystone Realtors Ltd that operates under the 'Rustomjee' brand.

news.title: Over 700 houses in Gurugram’s DLF areas will lose occupation certificates for layout violation
news.para: The district town planner (enforcement), Amit Madholia, formally wrote to his counterpart in the planning wing, urging them to revoke the OCs of the properties on the list and instruct the DLF management to disconnect water and sewer connections.
